BULBASAUR.name: Bulbasaur
BULBASAUR.pokedex: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

IVYSAUR.name: Ivysaur
IVYSAUR.pokedex: To support its weight, Ivysaur's legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it spends more time lying in the sunlight, it's a sign that the bud will bloom soon.

VENUSAUR.name: Venusaur
VENUSAUR.pokedex: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

CHARMANDER.name: Charmander
CHARMANDER.pokedex: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

CHARMELEON.name: Charmeleon
CHARMELEON.pokedex: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

CHARIZARD.name: Charizard
CHARIZARD.pokedex: If Charizard becomes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a whitish-blue color.

SQUIRTLE.name: Squirtle
SQUIRTLE.pokedex: Its shell is not just for protection. Its rounded shape and the grooves on its surface minimize resistance in water, enabling Squirtle to swim at high speeds.

WARTORTLE.name: Wartortle
WARTORTLE.pokedex: Its large tail is covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon's toughness in battle.

BLASTOISE.name: Blastoise
BLASTOISE.pokedex: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

CATERPIE.name: Caterpie
CATERPIE.pokedex: Its voracious appetite compels it to devour leaves bigger than itself without hesitation. It releases a terribly strong odor from its antennae.

METAPOD.name: Metapod
METAPOD.pokedex: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

BUTTERFREE.name: Butterfree
BUTTERFREE.pokedex: Water-repellent powder on its wings enables it to collect honey, even in the heaviest of rains.

WEEDLE.name: Weedle
WEEDLE.pokedex: Predators not warned off by its brightly-colored body are jabbed with the toxic barb on its head.

KAKUNA.name: Kakuna
KAKUNA.pokedex: It remains virtually immobile while it clings to a tree. However, on the inside, it busily prepares for evolution. This is evident from how hot its shell becomes.

BEEDRILL.name: Beedrill
BEEDRILL.pokedex: It prefers hit-and-run attacks using its powerful poison stingers, trying to evade blows to its fragile body.

PIDGEY.name: Pidgey
PIDGEY.pokedex: It has an extremely sharp sense of direction. It can unerringly return home to its nest, however far it may be removed from its familiar surroundings.

PIDGEOTTO.name: Pidgeotto
PIDGEOTTO.pokedex: This Pokémon flies around, patrolling its large territory. If its living space is violated, it shows no mercy in thoroughly punishing the foe with its sharp claws.

PIDGEOT.name: Pidgeot
PIDGEOT.pokedex: It spreads its gorgeous wings wide to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach 2.

RATTATA.name: Rattata
RATTATA.pokedex: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

RATICATE.name: Raticate
RATICATE.pokedex: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

SPEAROW.name: Spearow
SPEAROW.pokedex: Farmers whose fields are troubled by bug Pokémon appreciate Spearow for its vigorous appetite and look after it.

FEAROW.name: Fearow
FEAROW.pokedex: Its long neck and elongated beak are ideal for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves this extended and skinny beak to pluck prey.

EKANS.name: Ekans
EKANS.pokedex: Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare.

ARBOK.name: Arbok
ARBOK.pokedex: Transfixing prey with the face-like pattern on its belly, it binds and poisons the frightened victim.

PIKACHU.name: Pikachu
PIKACHU.pokedex: This intelligent Pokémon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.

RAICHU.name: Raichu
RAICHU.pokedex: If it stores too much electricity, its behavior turns aggressive. To avoid this, it occasionally discharges excess energy and calms itself down.

SANDSHREW.name: Sandshrew
SANDSHREW.pokedex: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, this Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

SANDSLASH.name: Sandslash
SANDSLASH.pokedex: Its claws and horns often break off. The broken claws and horns can be used to carve plows for tilling farm fields.

NIDORANfE.name: Nidoran-F
NIDORANfE.pokedex: Its highly toxic barbs are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

NIDORINA.name: Nidorina
NIDORINA.pokedex: When Nidorina are with friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. It becomes nervous if separated from the others.

NIDOQUEEN.name: Nidoqueen
NIDOQUEEN.pokedex: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

NIDORANmA.name: Nidoran-M
NIDORANmA.pokedex: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

NIDORINO.name: Nidorino
NIDORINO.pokedex: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

NIDOKING.name: Nidoking
NIDOKING.pokedex: When it goes on a rampage, it's impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it's lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

CLEFAIRY.name: Clefairy
CLEFAIRY.pokedex: On every night of a full moon they come out to play. When dawn arrives, they return to their quiet mountain retreats and sleep nestled up against each other.

CLEFABLE.name: Clefable
CLEFABLE.pokedex: A Clefable uses its wings to skip lightly as if it were flying. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. On quiet, moonlit nights, it strolls on lakes.

VULPIX.name: Vulpix
VULPIX.pokedex: From its mouth spew flames that seem to resemble the spirits of the deceased. Some people mistakenly think this fire is a ghost.

NINETALES.name: Ninetales
NINETALES.pokedex: Legend has it that this mystical Pokémon was formed when nine saints coalesced into one.

JIGGLYPUFF.name: Jigglypuff
JIGGLYPUFF.pokedex: By freely changing the wavelength of its voice, Jigglypuff sings a mysterious melody sure to make any listener sleepy.

WIGGLYTUFF.name: Wigglytuff
WIGGLYTUFF.pokedex: The surfaces of its saucerlike eyes are always covered with a thin layer of tears. If any dust gets in this Pokémon's eyes, it is quickly washed away.

ZUBAT.name: Zubat
ZUBAT.pokedex: Their skin is so thin that they'll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another's bodies.

GOLBAT.name: Golbat
GOLBAT.pokedex: Its thick fangs are hollow like straws, making them unexpectedly fragile. These fangs are specialized for sucking blood.

ODDISH.name: Oddish
ODDISH.pokedex: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

GLOOM.name: Gloom
GLOOM.pokedex: A horribly noxious honey drools from its mouth. One whiff of the honey can result in memory loss. Some fans are said to enjoy this overwhelming stink, however.

VILEPLUME.name: Vileplume
VILEPLUME.pokedex: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.

PARAS.name: Paras
PARAS.pokedex: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

PARASECT.name: Parasect
PARASECT.pokedex: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

VENONAT.name: Venonat
VENONAT.pokedex: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

VENOMOTH.name: Venomoth
VENOMOTH.pokedex: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

DIGLETT.name: Diglett
DIGLETT.pokedex: Around their crops, farmers plant trees that Diglett like to eat as a way of getting Diglett to plow the fields for them.

DUGTRIO.name: Dugtrio
DUGTRIO.pokedex: Dugtrio's heads are sleek and smooth and incredibly hard. It can dig through any soil with its headbutts.

MEOWTH.name: Meowth
MEOWTH.pokedex: It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can make friends with Meowth easily. But it's fickle, so you can't count on that friendship lasting.

PERSIAN.name: Persian
PERSIAN.pokedex: Behind its lithe, elegant appearance lies a barbaric side. It will tear apart its prey on a mere whim.

PSYDUCK.name: Psyduck
PSYDUCK.pokedex: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.

GOLDUCK.name: Golduck
GOLDUCK.pokedex: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use telekinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.

MANKEY.name: Mankey
MANKEY.pokedex: It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.

PRIMEAPE.name: Primeape
PRIMEAPE.pokedex: It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.

GROWLITHE.name: Growlithe
GROWLITHE.pokedex: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

ARCANINE.name: Arcanine
ARCANINE.pokedex: Legends tell of it fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country. Those hearing its bark feel compelled to grovel before it.

POLIWAG.name: Poliwag
POLIWAG.pokedex: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

POLIWHIRL.name: Poliwhirl
POLIWHIRL.pokedex: This Pokémon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.

POLIWRATH.name: Poliwrath
POLIWRATH.pokedex: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.

ABRA.name: Abra
ABRA.pokedex: It can read others' minds and will teleport away when danger approaches. You must clear your mind if you want to catch it.

KADABRA.name: Kadabra
KADABRA.pokedex: It stares at a silver spoon to amplify its psychic powers before it lets loose. Apparently, gold spoons are no good.

ALAKAZAM.name: Alakazam
ALAKAZAM.pokedex: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.

MACHOP.name: Machop
MACHOP.pokedex: Machop exercises by hefting around a Graveler as if it were a barbell. There are some Machop that travel the world in a quest to master all kinds of martial arts.

MACHOKE.name: Machoke
MACHOKE.pokedex: Machoke works out every day even as it helps with tough labor. On its days off, this Pokémon heads to the fields and mountains to exercise and train.

MACHAMP.name: Machamp
MACHAMP.pokedex: It can lift heavy loads with the greatest of ease. It can even heft dump trucks. But its clumsy fingers prevent it from doing any precision work.

BELLSPROUT.name: Bellsprout
BELLSPROUT.pokedex: Bellsprout's thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

WEEPINBELL.name: Weepinbell
WEEPINBELL.pokedex: If its prey is bigger than its mouth, it slices up the victim with sharp leaves, then eats every morsel.

VICTREEBEL.name: Victreebel
VICTREEBEL.pokedex: It attracts prey with aromatic honey, then melts them in its mouth. Acid that has dissolved many prey becomes sweeter, making it even more alluring.

TENTACOOL.name: Tentacool
TENTACOOL.pokedex: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

TENTACRUEL.name: Tentacruel
TENTACRUEL.pokedex: It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it's a warning sign.

GEODUDE.name: Geodude
GEODUDE.pokedex: The longer it lives, the more its edges are chipped and worn away. However, this Pokémon's heart will remain hard, craggy, and rough always.

GRAVELER.name: Graveler
GRAVELER.pokedex: This Pokémon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.

GOLEM.name: Golem
GOLEM.pokedex: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.

PONYTA.name: Ponyta
PONYTA.pokedex: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.

RAPIDASH.name: Rapidash
RAPIDASH.pokedex: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

SLOWPOKE.name: Slowpoke
SLOWPOKE.pokedex: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in rivers. However, it often forgets what it's doing and spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.

SLOWBRO.name: Slowbro
SLOWBRO.pokedex: A metamorphosed Shellder has latched onto Slowbro's tail. The tail can't be used for fishing anymore, forcing Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.

MAGNEMITE.name: Magnemite
MAGNEMITE.pokedex: It's frequently the cause of power outages, which is why some power plants send out electrical signals that it can't stand.

MAGNETON.name: Magneton
MAGNETON.pokedex: When rain clouds form, many Magneton gather in high places to wait for lightning to strike.

FARFETCHD.name: Farfetch'd
FARFETCHD.pokedex: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

DODUO.name: Doduo
DODUO.pokedex: By alternately raising and lowering its two heads, it balances itself to be more stable while running.

DODRIO.name: Dodrio
DODRIO.pokedex: It collects data and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and fall into a state of immobility.

SEEL.name: Seel
SEEL.pokedex: Seel hunts in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it breaks through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

DEWGONG.name: Dewgong
DEWGONG.pokedex: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

GRIMER.name: Grimer
GRIMER.pokedex: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokémon's numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

MUK.name: Muk
MUK.pokedex: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.

SHELLDER.name: Shellder
SHELLDER.pokedex: This Pokémon's tongue is always hanging out. It uses its tongue with great dexterity to dig up sand from the seabed in its search for food.

CLOYSTER.name: Cloyster
CLOYSTER.pokedex: Cloyster swims by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. It shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

GASTLY.name: Gastly
GASTLY.pokedex: When exposed to a strong wind, a Gastly's gaseous body quickly dwindles away. They cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.

HAUNTER.name: Haunter
HAUNTER.pokedex: On moonless nights, Haunter searches for someone to curse, so it's best not to go out walking around.

GENGAR.name: Gengar
GENGAR.pokedex: Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.

ONIX.name: Onix
ONIX.pokedex: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling.

DROWZEE.name: Drowzee
DROWZEE.pokedex: A Pokémon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.

HYPNO.name: Hypno
HYPNO.pokedex: While it is an extremely dangerous Pokémon, people who are in need of a good, sound sleep call it their savior.

KRABBY.name: Krabby
KRABBY.pokedex: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

KINGLER.name: Kingler
KINGLER.pokedex: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw, which it waves in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, it quickly tires.

VOLTORB.name: Voltorb
VOLTORB.pokedex: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

ELECTRODE.name: Electrode
ELECTRODE.pokedex: They appear in great numbers at electric power plants. Because they feed on electricity, they cause massive and chaotic blackouts in nearby cities.

EXEGGCUTE.name: Exeggcute
EXEGGCUTE.pokedex: These Pokémon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

EXEGGUTOR.name: Exeggutor
EXEGGUTOR.pokedex: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

CUBONE.name: Cubone
CUBONE.pokedex: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone's dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

MAROWAK.name: Marowak
MAROWAK.pokedex: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

HITMONLEE.name: Hitmonlee
HITMONLEE.pokedex: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

HITMONCHAN.name: Hitmonchan
HITMONCHAN.pokedex: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

LICKITUNG.name: Lickitung
LICKITUNG.pokedex: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it's really clean is... questionable.

KOFFING.name: Koffing
KOFFING.pokedex: Getting up close to a Koffing will give you a chance to observe, through its thin skin, the toxic gasses swirling inside. It blows up at the slightest stimulation.

WEEZING.name: Weezing
WEEZING.pokedex: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gasses by diluting them to the highest level.

RHYHORN.name: Rhyhorn
RHYHORN.pokedex: It is so dense, while on a run it forgets why it started running in the first place. It apparently remembers sometimes if it demolishes something.

RHYDON.name: Rhydon
RHYDON.pokedex: Rhydon has a horn that serves as a drill. This Pokémon occasionally rams into streams of magma, but the armor-like hide prevents it from feeling the heat.

CHANSEY.name: Chansey
CHANSEY.pokedex: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

TANGELA.name: Tangela
TANGELA.pokedex: Its vines snap off easily and painlessly if they are grabbed, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by new growth the very next day.

KANGASKHAN.name: Kangaskhan
KANGASKHAN.pokedex: Although it's carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

HORSEA.name: Horsea
HORSEA.pokedex: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

SEADRA.name: Seadra
SEADRA.pokedex: It's the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

GOLDEEN.name: Goldeen
GOLDEEN.pokedex: Although known for their splendid tail fins, Goldeen apparently compete among themselves to see whose horn is thickest and sharpest.

SEAKING.name: Seaking
SEAKING.pokedex: Trainers who are crazy for Seaking are divided into horn enthusiasts and fin enthusiasts. The two groups do not get along well.

STARYU.name: Staryu
STARYU.pokedex: This Pokémon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it's unconcerned by their snack attacks.

STARMIE.name: Starmie
STARMIE.pokedex: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

MRMIME.name: Mr. Mime
MRMIME.pokedex: Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.

SCYTHER.name: Scyther
SCYTHER.pokedex: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

JYNX.name: Jynx
JYNX.pokedex: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

ELECTABUZZ.name: Electabuzz
ELECTABUZZ.pokedex: While it's often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.

MAGMAR.name: Magmar
MAGMAR.pokedex: When it breathes deeply, heat mirages form around its body, making it hard to see clearly.

PINSIR.name: Pinsir
PINSIR.pokedex: Although it's tough, it can't handle cold well. When night falls, it buries itself in leafage and sleeps.

TAUROS.name: Tauros
TAUROS.pokedex: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it's a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

MAGIKARP.name: Magikarp
MAGIKARP.pokedex: Its swimming muscles are weak, so it is easily washed away by currents. In places where water pools, you can see many Magikarp deposited there by the flow.

GYARADOS.name: Gyarados
GYARADOS.pokedex: Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

LAPRAS.name: Lapras
LAPRAS.pokedex: Once endangered, they are now overabundant. Their mournful songs have died out as the population rebounds.

DITTO.name: Ditto
DITTO.pokedex: With its astonishing capacity for metamorphosis, it can get along with anything - except for its fellow Ditto.

EEVEE.name: Eevee
EEVEE.pokedex: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives.

VAPOREON.name: Vaporeon
VAPOREON.pokedex: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

JOLTEON.name: Jolteon
JOLTEON.pokedex: Its lungs contain an organ that creates electricity. The crackling sound of electricity can be heard when it exhales.

FLAREON.name: Flareon
FLAREON.pokedex: A dedicated omnivore, Flareon will eat anything - as long as it's been slow-roasted first.

PORYGON.name: Porygon
PORYGON.pokedex: This Pokémon was created using the cutting-edge science of 20 years ago, so many parts of it have since become obsolete.

OMANYTE.name: Omanyte
OMANYTE.pokedex: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.

OMASTAR.name: Omastar
OMASTAR.pokedex: Its heavy shell is thought to be the reason this ancient Pokémon died out. It's apparently a distant ancestor of Octillery.

KABUTO.name: Kabuto
KABUTO.pokedex: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

KABUTOPS.name: Kabutops
KABUTOPS.pokedex: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

AERODACTYL.name: Aerodactyl
AERODACTYL.pokedex: It flew through the open skies over the ancient continent as if they were its own. When it touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.

SNORLAX.name: Snorlax
SNORLAX.pokedex: Its stomach is said to be incomparably strong. Even Muk's poison is nothing more than a hint of spice on Snorlax's tongue.

ARTICUNO.name: Articuno
ARTICUNO.pokedex: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

ZAPDOS.name: Zapdos
ZAPDOS.pokedex: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear only when a thundercloud parts into two halves.

MOLTRES.name: Moltres
MOLTRES.pokedex: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

DRATINI.name: Dratini
DRATINI.pokedex: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

DRAGONAIR.name: Dragonair
DRAGONAIR.pokedex: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity via crystals on its neck and tail.

DRAGONITE.name: Dragonite
DRAGONITE.pokedex: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

MEWTWO.name: Mewtwo
MEWTWO.pokedex: Created from the DNA of Mew, this Pokémon is a dangerous combination of overwhelming power and a savage heart.

MEW.name: Mew
MEW.pokedex: It's very intelligent and can use an incredible variety of moves. Many believe that all other Pokémon are descendants of this one.

CHIKORITA.name: Chikorita
CHIKORITA.pokedex: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

BAYLEEF.name: Bayleef
BAYLEEF.pokedex: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

MEGANIUM.name: Meganium
MEGANIUM.pokedex: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

CYNDAQUIL.name: Cyndaquil
CYNDAQUIL.pokedex: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

QUILAVA.name: Quilava
QUILAVA.pokedex: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

TYPHLOSION.name: Typhlosion
TYPHLOSION.pokedex: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

TOTODILE.name: Totodile
TOTODILE.pokedex: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

CROCONAW.name: Croconaw
CROCONAW.pokedex: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

FERALIGATR.name: Feraligatr
FERALIGATR.pokedex: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

SENTRET.name: Sentret
SENTRET.pokedex: This Pokémon is very cautious. It stands on its tail in order to see enemies from far away. If it does then it alert its pack by thumping its tail on the ground.

FURRET.name: Furret
FURRET.pokedex: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. It uses tunnels in order to make a quick getaway from foes.

HOOTHOOT.name: Hoothoot
HOOTHOOT.pokedex: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

NOCTOWL.name: Noctowl
NOCTOWL.pokedex: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

LEDYBA.name: Ledyba
LEDYBA.pokedex: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

LEDIAN.name: Ledian
LEDIAN.pokedex: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

SPINARAK.name: Spinarak
SPINARAK.pokedex: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

ARIADOS.name: Ariados
ARIADOS.pokedex: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

CROBAT.name: Crobat
CROBAT.pokedex: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target's neck.

CHINCHOU.name: Chinchou
CHINCHOU.pokedex: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

LANTURN.name: Lanturn
LANTURN.pokedex: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

PICHU.name: Pichu
PICHU.pokedex: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

CLEFFA.name: Cleffa
CLEFFA.pokedex: Many appear when the night skies are filled with shooting stars. They disappear with sunrise.

IGGLYBUFF.name: Igglybuff
IGGLYBUFF.pokedex: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

TOGEPI.name: Togepi
TOGEPI.pokedex: Togepi shares its joy with the people who take care of it. It can act maliciously, causing havoc and bad luck to its enemies.

TOGETIC.name: Togetic
TOGETIC.pokedex: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

NATU.name: Natu
NATU.pokedex: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

XATU.name: Xatu
XATU.pokedex: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

MAREEP.name: Mareep
MAREEP.pokedex: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.

FLAAFFY.name: Flaaffy
FLAAFFY.pokedex: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

AMPHAROS.name: Ampharos
AMPHAROS.pokedex: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

BELLOSSOM.name: Bellossom
BELLOSSOM.pokedex: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

MARILL.name: Marill
MARILL.pokedex: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

AZUMARILL.name: Azumarill
AZUMARILL.pokedex: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it's in the water.

SUDOWOODO.name: Sudowoodo
SUDOWOODO.pokedex: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

POLITOED.name: Politoed
POLITOED.pokedex: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.

HOPPIP.name: Hoppip
HOPPIP.pokedex: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

SKIPLOOM.name: Skiploom
SKIPLOOM.pokedex: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

JUMPLUFF.name: Jumpluff
JUMPLUFF.pokedex: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

AIPOM.name: Aipom
AIPOM.pokedex: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

SUNKERN.name: Sunkern
SUNKERN.pokedex: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

SUNFLORA.name: Sunflora
SUNFLORA.pokedex: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

YANMA.name: Yanma
YANMA.pokedex: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

WOOPER.name: Wooper
WOOPER.pokedex: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.

QUAGSIRE.name: Quagsire
QUAGSIRE.pokedex: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

ESPEON.name: Espeon
ESPEON.pokedex: Its fur is so sensitive, it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weather...and its foes' thoughts.

UMBREON.name: Umbreon
UMBREON.pokedex: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.

MURKROW.name: Murkrow
MURKROW.pokedex: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

SLOWKING.name: Slowking
SLOWKING.pokedex: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

MISDREAVUS.name: Misdreavus
MISDREAVUS.pokedex: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

UNOWN.name: Unown
UNOWN.pokedex: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

WOBBUFFET.name: Wobbuffet
WOBBUFFET.pokedex: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

GIRAFARIG.name: Girafarig
GIRAFARIG.pokedex: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

PINECO.name: Pineco
PINECO.pokedex: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

FORRETRESS.name: Forretress
FORRETRESS.pokedex: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

DUNSPARCE.name: Dunsparce
DUNSPARCE.pokedex: Scientists believe that it used to fly with its wings during ancient times. Nowadays it burrows under the ground, sharing tunnels with other Pokémon.

GLIGAR.name: Gligar
GLIGAR.pokedex: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

STEELIX.name: Steelix
STEELIX.pokedex: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.

SNUBBULL.name: Snubbull
SNUBBULL.pokedex: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

GRANBULL.name: Granbull
GRANBULL.pokedex: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

QWILFISH.name: Qwilfish
QWILFISH.pokedex: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

SCIZOR.name: Scizor
SCIZOR.pokedex: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

SHUCKLE.name: Shuckle
SHUCKLE.pokedex: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

HERACROSS.name: Heracross
HERACROSS.pokedex: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

SNEASEL.name: Sneasel
SNEASEL.pokedex: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

TEDDIURSA.name: Teddiursa
TEDDIURSA.pokedex: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

URSARING.name: Ursaring
URSARING.pokedex: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

SLUGMA.name: Slugma
SLUGMA.pokedex: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

MAGCARGO.name: Magcargo
MAGCARGO.pokedex: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

SWINUB.name: Swinub
SWINUB.pokedex: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

PILOSWINE.name: Piloswine
PILOSWINE.pokedex: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

CORSOLA.name: Corsola
CORSOLA.pokedex: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

REMORAID.name: Remoraid
REMORAID.pokedex: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

OCTILLERY.name: Octillery
OCTILLERY.pokedex: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

DELIBIRD.name: Delibird
DELIBIRD.pokedex: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.

MANTINE.name: Mantine
MANTINE.pokedex: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

SKARMORY.name: Skarmory
SKARMORY.pokedex: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.

HOUNDOUR.name: Houndour
HOUNDOUR.pokedex: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

HOUNDOOM.name: Houndoom
HOUNDOOM.pokedex: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

KINGDRA.name: Kingdra
KINGDRA.pokedex: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.

PHANPY.name: Phanpy
PHANPY.pokedex: Phanpy uses its snout to shower itself with water. However its snout is so strong that when it bumps into you, it may send you flying.

DONPHAN.name: Donphan
DONPHAN.pokedex: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

PORYGON2.name: Porygon2
PORYGON2.pokedex: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

STANTLER.name: Stantler
STANTLER.pokedex: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.

SMEARGLE.name: Smeargle
SMEARGLE.pokedex: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

TYROGUE.name: Tyrogue
TYROGUE.pokedex: To brush up on its fighting skills, it will challenge anyone. It has a very strong competitive spirit.

HITMONTOP.name: Hitmontop
HITMONTOP.pokedex: If you are enchanted by its smooth, dance-like kicks, you may get a closer experience with one than you'd like.

SMOOCHUM.name: Smoochum
SMOOCHUM.pokedex: If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn't really seem to care.

ELEKID.name: Elekid
ELEKID.pokedex: It's not good at storing electricity yet. This Pokémon sneaks into people's homes, looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.

MAGBY.name: Magby
MAGBY.pokedex: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.

MILTANK.name: Miltank
MILTANK.pokedex: Miltank's milk has been sought after due to its taste and nutrition. The local treat of Castelia City, Casteliacones, is made from fresh Moomoo Milk.

BLISSEY.name: Blissey
BLISSEY.pokedex: This kindhearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.

RAIKOU.name: Raikou
RAIKOU.pokedex: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

ENTEI.name: Entei
ENTEI.pokedex: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

SUICUNE.name: Suicune
SUICUNE.pokedex: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

LARVITAR.name: Larvitar
LARVITAR.pokedex: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

PUPITAR.name: Pupitar
PUPITAR.pokedex: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

TYRANITAR.name: Tyranitar
TYRANITAR.pokedex: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

LUGIA.name: Lugia
LUGIA.pokedex: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

HOOH.name: Ho-Oh
HOOH.pokedex: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

CELEBI.name: Celebi
CELEBI.pokedex: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.

TREECKO.name: Treecko
TREECKO.pokedex: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

GROVYLE.name: Grovyle
GROVYLE.pokedex: The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

SCEPTILE.name: Sceptile
SCEPTILE.pokedex: The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

TORCHIC.name: Torchic
TORCHIC.pokedex: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug - it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

COMBUSKEN.name: Combusken
COMBUSKEN.pokedex: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks.

BLAZIKEN.name: Blaziken
BLAZIKEN.pokedex: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs - it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon's blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

MUDKIP.name: Mudkip
MUDKIP.pokedex: In water, Mudkip breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this Pokémon will unleash its amazing power - it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

MARSHTOMP.name: Marshtomp
MARSHTOMP.pokedex: The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

SWAMPERT.name: Swampert
SWAMPERT.pokedex: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

POOCHYENA.name: Poochyena
POOCHYENA.pokedex: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

MIGHTYENA.name: Mightyena
MIGHTYENA.pokedex: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

ZIGZAGOON.name: Zigzagoon
ZIGZAGOON.pokedex: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.

LINOONE.name: Linoone
LINOONE.pokedex: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

WURMPLE.name: Wurmple
WURMPLE.pokedex: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

SILCOON.name: Silcoon
SILCOON.pokedex: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

BEAUTIFLY.name: Beautifly
BEAUTIFLY.pokedex: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

CASCOON.name: Cascoon
CASCOON.pokedex: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

DUSTOX.name: Dustox
DUSTOX.pokedex: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

LOTAD.name: Lotad
LOTAD.pokedex: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

LOMBRE.name: Lombre
LOMBRE.pokedex: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

LUDICOLO.name: Ludicolo
LUDICOLO.pokedex: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo's cells, making it more powerful.

SEEDOT.name: Seedot
SEEDOT.pokedex: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

NUZLEAF.name: Nuzleaf
NUZLEAF.pokedex: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

SHIFTRY.name: Shiftry
SHIFTRY.pokedex: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.

TAILLOW.name: Taillow
TAILLOW.pokedex: This Pokémon is very gutsy and will fight powerful opponents without backing down. On the other hand, when it is hungry it will weaken and cry loudly.

SWELLOW.name: Swellow
SWELLOW.pokedex: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

WINGULL.name: Wingull
WINGULL.pokedex: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

PELIPPER.name: Pelipper
PELIPPER.pokedex: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

RALTS.name: Ralts
RALTS.pokedex: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

KIRLIA.name: Kirlia
KIRLIA.pokedex: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

GARDEVOIR.name: Gardevoir
GARDEVOIR.pokedex: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

SURSKIT.name: Surskit
SURSKIT.pokedex: Its legs can generate oils, helping it glide through the water. The antenna on its head can secrete a thick, sugary syrup that is used to attract prey.

MASQUERAIN.name: Masquerain
MASQUERAIN.pokedex: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

SHROOMISH.name: Shroomish
SHROOMISH.pokedex: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

BRELOOM.name: Breloom
BRELOOM.pokedex: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

SLAKOTH.name: Slakoth
SLAKOTH.pokedex: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

VIGOROTH.name: Vigoroth
VIGOROTH.pokedex: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

SLAKING.name: Slaking
SLAKING.pokedex: It is the world's most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

NINCADA.name: Nincada
NINCADA.pokedex: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

NINJASK.name: Ninjask
NINJASK.pokedex: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

SHEDINJA.name: Shedinja
SHEDINJA.pokedex: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

WHISMUR.name: Whismur
WHISMUR.pokedex: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

LOUDRED.name: Loudred
LOUDRED.pokedex: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

EXPLOUD.name: Exploud
EXPLOUD.pokedex: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.

MAKUHITA.name: Makuhita
MAKUHITA.pokedex: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

HARIYAMA.name: Hariyama
HARIYAMA.pokedex: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

AZURILL.name: Azurill
AZURILL.pokedex: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

NOSEPASS.name: Nosepass
NOSEPASS.pokedex: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

SKITTY.name: Skitty
SKITTY.pokedex: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.

DELCATTY.name: Delcatty
DELCATTY.pokedex: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

SABLEYE.name: Sableye
SABLEYE.pokedex: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

MAWILE.name: Mawile
MAWILE.pokedex: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

ARON.name: Aron
ARON.pokedex: When Aron evolves, its steel armor peels off. In ancient times, people would collect Aron's shed armor and make good use of it in their daily lives.

LAIRON.name: Lairon
LAIRON.pokedex: During territorial disputes, Lairon fight by slamming into each other. Close inspection of their steel armor reveals scratches and dents.

AGGRON.name: Aggron
AGGRON.pokedex: Long ago, there was a king who wore a helmet meant to resemble the head of an Aggron. He was trying to channel the Pokémon's strength.

MEDITITE.name: Meditite
MEDITITE.pokedex: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

MEDICHAM.name: Medicham
MEDICHAM.pokedex: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

ELECTRIKE.name: Electrike
ELECTRIKE.pokedex: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

MANECTRIC.name: Manectric
MANECTRIC.pokedex: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

PLUSLE.name: Plusle
PLUSLE.pokedex: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

MINUN.name: Minun
MINUN.pokedex: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

VOLBEAT.name: Volbeat
VOLBEAT.pokedex: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

ILLUMISE.name: Illumise
ILLUMISE.pokedex: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

ROSELIA.name: Roselia
ROSELIA.pokedex: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

GULPIN.name: Gulpin
GULPIN.pokedex: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

SWALOT.name: Swalot
SWALOT.pokedex: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

CARVANHA.name: Carvanha
CARVANHA.pokedex: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enter its territory.

SHARPEDO.name: Sharpedo
SHARPEDO.pokedex: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

WAILMER.name: Wailmer
WAILMER.pokedex: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.

WAILORD.name: Wailord
WAILORD.pokedex: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

NUMEL.name: Numel
NUMEL.pokedex: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

CAMERUPT.name: Camerupt
CAMERUPT.pokedex: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

TORKOAL.name: Torkoal
TORKOAL.pokedex: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

SPOINK.name: Spoink
SPOINK.pokedex: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

GRUMPIG.name: Grumpig
GRUMPIG.pokedex: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

SPINDA.name: Spinda
SPINDA.pokedex: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

TRAPINCH.name: Trapinch
TRAPINCH.pokedex: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

VIBRAVA.name: Vibrava
VIBRAVA.pokedex: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.

FLYGON.name: Flygon
FLYGON.pokedex: Known as "The Desert Spirit," this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.

CACNEA.name: Cacnea
CACNEA.pokedex: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

CACTURNE.name: Cacturne
CACTURNE.pokedex: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

SWABLU.name: Swablu
SWABLU.pokedex: Swablu is very friendly towards humans, so a Swablu may land on your head and act like a fluffy hat.

ALTARIA.name: Altaria
ALTARIA.pokedex: Altarias often glide through the clouds while singing or humming. While normally kind, Altaria will attack foes without mercy if provoked.

ZANGOOSE.name: Zangoose
ZANGOOSE.pokedex: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

SEVIPER.name: Seviper
SEVIPER.pokedex: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

LUNATONE.name: Lunatone
LUNATONE.pokedex: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

SOLROCK.name: Solrock
SOLROCK.pokedex: It absorbs solar energy during the day. Always expressionless, it can sense what its foe is thinking.

BARBOACH.name: Barboach
BARBOACH.pokedex: Its whiskers make a superb radar. They are used to locate prey, even in the murkiest of water.

WHISCASH.name: Whiscash
WHISCASH.pokedex: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything--if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

CORPHISH.name: Corphish
CORPHISH.pokedex: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

CRAWDAUNT.name: Crawdaunt
CRAWDAUNT.pokedex: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

BALTOY.name: Baltoy
BALTOY.pokedex: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

CLAYDOL.name: Claydol
CLAYDOL.pokedex: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

LILEEP.name: Lileep
LILEEP.pokedex: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

CRADILY.name: Cradily
CRADILY.pokedex: It has short legs and can't walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

ANORITH.name: Anorith
ANORITH.pokedex: Anorith can swim swiftly by pulling its eight wings through the water like oars on a boat. This Pokémon is an ancestor of modern bug Pokémon.

ARMALDO.name: Armaldo
ARMALDO.pokedex: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

FEEBAS.name: Feebas
FEEBAS.pokedex: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

MILOTIC.name: Milotic
MILOTIC.pokedex: It is the world's most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.

CASTFORM.name: Castform
CASTFORM.pokedex: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.

KECLEON.name: Kecleon
KECLEON.pokedex: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

SHUPPET.name: Shuppet
SHUPPET.pokedex: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

BANETTE.name: Banette
BANETTE.pokedex: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

DUSKULL.name: Duskull
DUSKULL.pokedex: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it's said.

DUSCLOPS.name: Dusclops
DUSCLOPS.pokedex: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.

TROPIUS.name: Tropius
TROPIUS.pokedex: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.

CHIMECHO.name: Chimecho
CHIMECHO.pokedex: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

ABSOL.name: Absol
ABSOL.pokedex: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

WYNAUT.name: Wynaut
WYNAUT.pokedex: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

SNORUNT.name: Snorunt
SNORUNT.pokedex: In Sinnoh, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a Snorunt lives there.

GLALIE.name: Glalie
GLALIE.pokedex: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

SPHEAL.name: Spheal
SPHEAL.pokedex: It's more efficient for Spheal to roll than to walk. When this Pokémon is happy, it claps its fins.

SEALEO.name: Sealeo
SEALEO.pokedex: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

WALREIN.name: Walrein
WALREIN.pokedex: Walrein's tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

CLAMPERL.name: Clamperl
CLAMPERL.pokedex: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

HUNTAIL.name: Huntail
HUNTAIL.pokedex: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

GOREBYSS.name: Gorebyss
GOREBYSS.pokedex: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

RELICANTH.name: Relicanth
RELICANTH.pokedex: This Pokémon was discovered during deep-sea exploration. Its appearance hasn't changed in 100,000,000 years, so it's called a living fossil.

LUVDISC.name: Luvdisc
LUVDISC.pokedex: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

BAGON.name: Bagon
BAGON.pokedex: Bagon is a solitary Pokémon that doesn't form groups with others of its kind. It also has a head hard enough to cleave a boulder in one strike.

SHELGON.name: Shelgon
SHELGON.pokedex: Shelgon ignores its hunger entirely, never eating any food. Apparently, Shelgon will evolve once all its energy stores are used up.

SALAMENCE.name: Salamence
SALAMENCE.pokedex: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps this Pokémon in high spirits, Salamence turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

BELDUM.name: Beldum
BELDUM.pokedex: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.

METANG.name: Metang
METANG.pokedex: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft, this Pokémon flies at high speeds, weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.

METAGROSS.name: Metagross
METAGROSS.pokedex: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokémon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

REGIROCK.name: Regirock
REGIROCK.pokedex: The third of the titans, built to commemorate an era of stonecraft. It is as resilient as an ancient monolith.

REGICE.name: Regice
REGICE.pokedex: The second of the titans, built to commemorate an era of ice. It is as implacable as an encroaching glacier.

REGISTEEL.name: Registeel
REGISTEEL.pokedex: The fourth of the titans, built to commemorate an era of metalworking. It is as unfailing as a master swordsmith's blade.

LATIAS.name: Latias
LATIAS.pokedex: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

LATIOS.name: Latios
LATIOS.pokedex: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

KYOGRE.name: Kyogre
KYOGRE.pokedex: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

GROUDON.name: Groudon
GROUDON.pokedex: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

RAYQUAZA.name: Rayquaza
RAYQUAZA.pokedex: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

JIRACHI.name: Jirachi
JIRACHI.pokedex: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

DEOXYS.name: Deoxys
DEOXYS.pokedex: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

TURTWIG.name: Turtwig
TURTWIG.pokedex: It relies heavily on water to keep its plant healthy, and thus it spends most of its time near lakes. When thirsty, the plant on its head wilts.

GROTLE.name: Grotle
GROTLE.pokedex: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

TORTERRA.name: Torterra
TORTERRA.pokedex: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

CHIMCHAR.name: Chimchar
CHIMCHAR.pokedex: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

MONFERNO.name: Monferno
MONFERNO.pokedex: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

INFERNAPE.name: Infernape
INFERNAPE.pokedex: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

PIPLUP.name: Piplup
PIPLUP.pokedex: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

PRINPLUP.name: Prinplup
PRINPLUP.pokedex: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

EMPOLEON.name: Empoleon
EMPOLEON.pokedex: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

STARLY.name: Starly
STARLY.pokedex: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

STARAVIA.name: Staravia
STARAVIA.pokedex: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

STARAPTOR.name: Staraptor
STARAPTOR.pokedex: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

BIDOOF.name: Bidoof
BIDOOF.pokedex: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

BIBAREL.name: Bibarel
BIBAREL.pokedex: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

KRICKETOT.name: Kricketot
KRICKETOT.pokedex: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

KRICKETUNE.name: Kricketune
KRICKETUNE.pokedex: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

SHINX.name: Shinx
SHINX.pokedex: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

LUXIO.name: Luxio
LUXIO.pokedex: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

LUXRAY.name: Luxray
LUXRAY.pokedex: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

BUDEW.name: Budew
BUDEW.pokedex: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

ROSERADE.name: Roserade
ROSERADE.pokedex: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

CRANIDOS.name: Cranidos
CRANIDOS.pokedex: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

RAMPARDOS.name: Rampardos
RAMPARDOS.pokedex: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

SHIELDON.name: Shieldon
SHIELDON.pokedex: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

BASTIODON.name: Bastiodon
BASTIODON.pokedex: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

BURMY.name: Burmy
BURMY.pokedex: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

WORMADAM.name: Wormadam
WORMADAM.pokedex: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

MOTHIM.name: Mothim
MOTHIM.pokedex: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

COMBEE.name: Combee
COMBEE.pokedex: It collects honey for its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep. If a colony loses their Vespiquen, a new Combee will take its place.

VESPIQUEN.name: Vespiquen
VESPIQUEN.pokedex: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

PACHIRISU.name: Pachirisu
PACHIRISU.pokedex: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

BUIZEL.name: Buizel
BUIZEL.pokedex: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

FLOATZEL.name: Floatzel
FLOATZEL.pokedex: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

CHERUBI.name: Cherubi
CHERUBI.pokedex: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

CHERRIM.name: Cherrim
CHERRIM.pokedex: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

SHELLOS.name: Shellos
SHELLOS.pokedex: The colors of this Pokémon change depending on its environment. When it senses danger, this Pokémon excretes a sticky purple liquid.

GASTRODON.name: Gastrodon
GASTRODON.pokedex: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

AMBIPOM.name: Ambipom
AMBIPOM.pokedex: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

DRIFLOON.name: Drifloon
DRIFLOON.pokedex: These Pokémon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.

DRIFBLIM.name: Drifblim
DRIFBLIM.pokedex: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

BUNEARY.name: Buneary
BUNEARY.pokedex: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

LOPUNNY.name: Lopunny
LOPUNNY.pokedex: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

MISMAGIUS.name: Mismagius
MISMAGIUS.pokedex: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

HONCHKROW.name: Honchkrow
HONCHKROW.pokedex: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

GLAMEOW.name: Glameow
GLAMEOW.pokedex: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

PURUGLY.name: Purugly
PURUGLY.pokedex: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

CHINGLING.name: Chingling
CHINGLING.pokedex: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

STUNKY.name: Stunky
STUNKY.pokedex: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

SKUNTANK.name: Skuntank
SKUNTANK.pokedex: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

BRONZOR.name: Bronzor
BRONZOR.pokedex: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

BRONZONG.name: Bronzong
BRONZONG.pokedex: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

BONSLY.name: Bonsly
BONSLY.pokedex: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

MIMEJR.name: Mime Jr.
MIMEJR.pokedex: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

HAPPINY.name: Happiny
HAPPINY.pokedex: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

CHATOT.name: Chatot
CHATOT.pokedex: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

SPIRITOMB.name: Spiritomb
SPIRITOMB.pokedex: All Spiritomb's mischief and misdeeds compelled a traveler to use a mysterious spell to bind Spiritomb to an odd keystone.

GIBLE.name: Gible
GIBLE.pokedex: Gible attacks anything that moves, and it drags whatever it catches into the crevice that is its lair. Despite the big mouth, Gible's stomach is small.

GABITE.name: Gabite
GABITE.pokedex: Jewels are buried in the caves these Pokémon nest in, but you'll be torn apart by claws and fangs the moment you enter one of these caves.

GARCHOMP.name: Garchomp
GARCHOMP.pokedex: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

MUNCHLAX.name: Munchlax
MUNCHLAX.pokedex: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

RIOLU.name: Riolu
RIOLU.pokedex: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

LUCARIO.name: Lucario
LUCARIO.pokedex: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

HIPPOPOTAS.name: Hippopotas
HIPPOPOTAS.pokedex: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

HIPPOWDON.name: Hippowdon
HIPPOWDON.pokedex: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

SKORUPI.name: Skorupi
SKORUPI.pokedex: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

DRAPION.name: Drapion
DRAPION.pokedex: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

CROAGUNK.name: Croagunk
CROAGUNK.pokedex: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

TOXICROAK.name: Toxicroak
TOXICROAK.pokedex: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

CARNIVINE.name: Carnivine
CARNIVINE.pokedex: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

FINNEON.name: Finneon
FINNEON.pokedex: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

LUMINEON.name: Lumineon
LUMINEON.pokedex: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

MANTYKE.name: Mantyke
MANTYKE.pokedex: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

SNOVER.name: Snover
SNOVER.pokedex: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

ABOMASNOW.name: Abomasnow
ABOMASNOW.pokedex: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

WEAVILE.name: Weavile
WEAVILE.pokedex: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

MAGNEZONE.name: Magnezone
MAGNEZONE.pokedex: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

LICKILICKY.name: Lickilicky
LICKILICKY.pokedex: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

RHYPERIOR.name: Rhyperior
RHYPERIOR.pokedex: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

TANGROWTH.name: Tangrowth
TANGROWTH.pokedex: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

ELECTIVIRE.name: Electivire
ELECTIVIRE.pokedex: In terms of electrical-energy output, Electivire is one of the best among all Electric Pokémon. It discharges high-voltage currents from its tails.

MAGMORTAR.name: Magmortar
MAGMORTAR.pokedex: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

TOGEKISS.name: Togekiss
TOGEKISS.pokedex: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

YANMEGA.name: Yanmega
YANMEGA.pokedex: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

LEAFEON.name: Leafeon
LEAFEON.pokedex: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

GLACEON.name: Glaceon
GLACEON.pokedex: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

GLISCOR.name: Gliscor
GLISCOR.pokedex: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

MAMOSWINE.name: Mamoswine
MAMOSWINE.pokedex: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

PORYGONZ.name: Porygon-Z
PORYGONZ.pokedex: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

GALLADE.name: Gallade
GALLADE.pokedex: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

PROBOPASS.name: Probopass
PROBOPASS.pokedex: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

DUSKNOIR.name: Dusknoir
DUSKNOIR.pokedex: It comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife.

FROSLASS.name: Froslass
FROSLASS.pokedex: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

ROTOM.name: Rotom
ROTOM.pokedex: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

UXIE.name: Uxie
UXIE.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

MESPRIT.name: Mesprit
MESPRIT.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

AZELF.name: Azelf
AZELF.pokedex: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

DIALGA.name: Dialga
DIALGA.pokedex: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

PALKIA.name: Palkia
PALKIA.pokedex: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

HEATRAN.name: Heatran
HEATRAN.pokedex: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

REGIGIGAS.name: Regigigas
REGIGIGAS.pokedex: The creator of the titans, who shaped the primal clay in the golden age. Its creative powers are boundless.

GIRATINA.name: Giratina
GIRATINA.pokedex: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

CRESSELIA.name: Cresselia
CRESSELIA.pokedex: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

PHIONE.name: Phione
PHIONE.pokedex: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

MANAPHY.name: Manaphy
MANAPHY.pokedex: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

DARKRAI.name: Darkrai
DARKRAI.pokedex: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

SHAYMIN.name: Shaymin
SHAYMIN.pokedex: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

ARCEUS.name: Arceus
ARCEUS.pokedex: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

VICTINI.name: Victini
VICTINI.pokedex: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

SNIVY.name: Snivy
SNIVY.pokedex: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

SERVINE.name: Servine
SERVINE.pokedex: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

SERPERIOR.name: Serperior
SERPERIOR.pokedex: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

TEPIG.name: Tepig
TEPIG.pokedex: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

PIGNITE.name: Pignite
PIGNITE.pokedex: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

EMBOAR.name: Emboar
EMBOAR.pokedex: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

OSHAWOTT.name: Oshawott
OSHAWOTT.pokedex: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

DEWOTT.name: Dewott
DEWOTT.pokedex: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

SAMUROTT.name: Samurott
SAMUROTT.pokedex: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

PATRAT.name: Patrat
PATRAT.pokedex: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

WATCHOG.name: Watchog
WATCHOG.pokedex: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

LILLIPUP.name: Lillipup
LILLIPUP.pokedex: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

HERDIER.name: Herdier
HERDIER.pokedex: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

STOUTLAND.name: Stoutland
STOUTLAND.pokedex: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

PURRLOIN.name: Purrloin
PURRLOIN.pokedex: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

LIEPARD.name: Liepard
LIEPARD.pokedex: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

PANSAGE.name: Pansage
PANSAGE.pokedex: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

SIMISAGE.name: Simisage
SIMISAGE.pokedex: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

PANSEAR.name: Pansear
PANSEAR.pokedex: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

SIMISEAR.name: Simisear
SIMISEAR.pokedex: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

PANPOUR.name: Panpour
PANPOUR.pokedex: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

SIMIPOUR.name: Simipour
SIMIPOUR.pokedex: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

MUNNA.name: Munna
MUNNA.pokedex: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

MUSHARNA.name: Musharna
MUSHARNA.pokedex: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

PIDOVE.name: Pidove
PIDOVE.pokedex: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

TRANQUILL.name: Tranquill
TRANQUILL.pokedex: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

UNFEZANT.name: Unfezant
UNFEZANT.pokedex: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

BLITZLE.name: Blitzle
BLITZLE.pokedex: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

ZEBSTRIKA.name: Zebstrika
ZEBSTRIKA.pokedex: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

ROGGENROLA.name: Roggenrola
ROGGENROLA.pokedex: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

BOLDORE.name: Boldore
BOLDORE.pokedex: The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it's not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.

GIGALITH.name: Gigalith
GIGALITH.pokedex: In Makyan myth, they were born from meteors that fell when the moon was split by an angry god. Their unfathomably dense armor deflects most anything.

WOOBAT.name: Woobat
WOOBAT.pokedex: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

SWOOBAT.name: Swoobat
SWOOBAT.pokedex: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

DRILBUR.name: Drilbur
